reviews.review_text: Good Recording Thanks! Good show, better recording.

Good Show.  Best Recording. I agree with yamarva about the show and the recording, though Jerry is just barely holding it together vocally.  Thankfully he does, which allows me to recommend this evening's entertainment.  Holding it together still only gives him a marginal tonality.  

This recording is a bit stark.  But adding a little reverb and some extra bass does wonders for Jer’s singing and the show overall.  Gives it a slightly mellower and more pleasant sound.  Always enjoy Jack Straw and Cold Rain openings.  And tonight we get them both!  Round & Round was a bit of a letdown at the end, so I spliced and faded in U.S. Blues after Black Peter.
